<br>
Palllys who tank must be VERY friendly with their stun keys.  You will use them a LOT.  If you have a pally that isn't holding agro, it is time to find a new tank AND make sure this person never tanks again.  They OBVIOUSLY don't know how.<br>
<br>
Warriors are being ripped off BIG time.  To my knowldege, all they have is taunt and DPS to hold agro.  One hard nuke, slow, tash, or failed mez and its bye bye mob.  I have seen wariors get it back, but too many times I have had to STOP attacking so they can get agro off of me.  I'm thinking &quot;Maybe I should just tank&quot;.<br>
<br>
Shadow Knights (like me).  We don't have just spear for gaining agro.  As a matter of a fact, if a SK is only using his/her spear line to hold agro, (s)he needs to give up their SK status, and go flog themselves with flaming electrical cords until I get there to hit them with rubber mallets.  SKs have jolts (ours ADD agro-list points by the several hundred per cast) visage buffs (increases your taunt by 5-10%) darkness (one of the highest agro spells in the game) and fear (RIGHT behind darkness in the agro category).  I hear that we are given hate list points just BECAUSE we are SKs (don't actually know how true this is).  Any time I have lost agro, I had it back within a cast and a taunt, IF even the taunt.  The problem is that people PL SKs right to the top, then they think they suck becasue they aren't warriors with nukes.  It doesn't work like that.  Any SK that tries to tank like a warrior will be a dead SK.  We have taps over time (not a hell fo a lot of agro, but REALLY helps the healer) tap buffs. and ... taps.  From what I can tell, we have more damage avoidance AAs than any other class, except MAYBE Pallys, and I'm not really sure about that one yet.<br>
<br>
I don't know how to tell you how to find good tanks, since I usually tank.  I know how to tank, and I hold agro quite well.  Anytime I have a ranger in group, I ask them to stay behind the mob and just do their insane DPS.  Maybe sling a heal when needed, but fo rthe most part, do what they do best.  Make those mobs look like pin-cushions.<br>
