Also, chanter and shammy are suppose to get hit.  If they play their class from level 1 up, they know they will get hit and they expect it.  Their gears are tuned towards HPs and they have their means (rune, root, heal, etc.) to take care of themselves.<br>
<br>
Unlike low level where you have to &quot;protect&quot; your healer/slower/mezzer, at high low they can take care of themselves.  If you are the MT, your focus is on your target, not to go around switching target and trying to taunt mobs off other people.  Cleric, chanter, and shammy are hardier than you think.  Let them do their job and you do yours.  The last thing the other DPS classes need is for the MT to switch target.<br>
<br>
